programmes.show_description: Axe Murder House. When Ian dares to visit The Villisca Axe Murder House, he's given a night he'll never forget. Plus, in England, Alyss goes for a regretful walk in the woods. S4, Ep6
Black Monk Ghost. A couple visits 30 East Drive, the most haunted house in the UK and the home of the demonic Black Monk. In Nottingham, Coral is in contact with otherworldly beings. S4, Ep7

Vancouver. The buyers bid on seized items and property at a police auction in Vancouver. Mark is interested in a magnetic drill while Billy and the Martins battle for vintage comics. S1, Ep9
NYC Transit. The buyers are at the New York City transit auction that contains 14,000 items. Billy and the Martins compete for a Stradivarius violin possibly worth $1 million. S1, Ep10
Bunny Money. The baggage battlers head to an auction in Denver, where they duel over a zebra rug. They also show an interest in some sealed lots, but will the contents be of value? S3, Ep10
World War Score. The Baggage Battlers are heading to the Normandy where the largest private collection of military artefacts is being put up for sale. What will they manage to buy? S3, Ep11
Golden Ticket. The baggage battlers hunt down bargains at an estate auction in Nashville, Tennessee. Will Billy be tempted by a mystery box with the inscription New Orleans, Tahiti? S3, Ep14
Swami Says. The buyers are once again on the road in search of profit, this time at an estate auction in Texas. Unique, high-end merchandise is the order of the day in Austin. S4, Ep1
Inflated Egos. The buyers return to Georgia, but this time take their auction battle out of Atlanta to the city of Commerce. Artefacts and iconic advertising pieces are up for grabs. S4, Ep2
Intergalactic Bounty. An eclectic mix of items calls to the buyers, drawing them back once again to do battle in Nashville. Items include a box full of license plates. S4, Ep3
Steal Drum. The buyers are once again in Nashville, TN. Billy, Mark, Laurence and Sally have returned to Music City Auction for all the great items that always seem to be on offer. S4, Ep4
Monster Money. The buyers are in Hollywood for one of the largest movie monster memorabilia auctions of all time. Items include pieces from Frankenstein and Wolf Man movies. S4, Ep5
10 Million Dollar Fixer Upper. Wayne and the team join a multi-shop mission get a coveted, seven-figure 1937 Bugatti ready for the most prestigious exhibition in the world. S11, Ep7
Twist And Scout. Wayne buys the motorcycle of his dreams, an all-original 1928 Indian Scout 101. Plus, he finds homes for a 1977 Mercedes 450 and an Audi R8. S11, Ep8
Let The Good Times Roll. The Cars' drummer David Robinson rolls into F40 with a restoration job on a rare 1969 De Tomaso Mangusta. How will they shake it up with this classic ride? S11, Ep9
Eclectic Avenue. During a hunt for the perfect '32 Ford, Wayne finds a vintage ice-cutting machine with a motorcycle body and engine. Plus, he uncovers a Bugatti Type 55s replica. S11, Ep10
It's Getting Hot In Here. It's the last car show of the season. The Fairlane and the Nomad get extra attention and Dave and Kevin check out the best cars in Reno. S4, Ep13
The Future Is Now. A '32 roadster bought for a client's wife is secretly shipped to Kindig It for upgrades and styling changes. A 2004 Hummer arrives for a futuristic redesign! S4, Ep14
The Secret Client. Dave is tasked with finding and transforming a 1967 GTO for a secret client from South Africa. Meanwhile, Dave buys back one of his first builds, a Karman Ghia. S4, Ep15
Ford Thunderbird: American Icon. A 1964 T-Bird needs pricey American parts to restore it to its former glory. And Ant gets a hand from his mate, Mike Brewer. S1, Ep7
Land Rover: A Favourite To Finish. Ant finds a rare 1978 Land Rover Series 3, a dream find for a Landie fanatic. But the bulkhead is riddled with rust, which could dent Ant's profit. S1, Ep8
NASA's Lost Treasure. Jeremy explores the loss of a NASA space capsule deep in the Atlantic. And, what is the underwater secret behind ship disappearances in the Devil's Sea? S1, Ep10
The Loch Ness Conspiracy. Jeremy explores a revolutionary technique that could identify the Loch Ness Monster. Plus, how did a man survive for several days trapped in a shipwreck? S1, Ep1
The Wendigo. Paranormal investigators reveal a bold new theory about the origins of the Wendigo. Are the stories of this terrifying creature with cannibalistic cravings true? S1, Ep5
The Yeti. Experts investigate evidence suggesting that one of the world's most elusive figures, the Yeti, lives in America and may have an otherworldly source. S1, Ep6
Into The Alien Ocean. Jess and Phil's investigation into unidentified objects off Catalina Island's coast heats up after the discovery of an extra-terrestrial underwater base. S2, Ep12
Ghosts In The Canal. Josh wants to investigate ghostly sightings and terrifying sounds coming from an abandoned canal along the Potomac. What will they uncover? S2, Ep13
Terror In Appalachia. Phil and Jess venture into the Great Smoky Mountains to investigate missing hiker reports and sightings of grotesque human-like creatures. S3, Ep1

Toronto. The buyers bid against one another for lost airport items in Toronto. Mark and Billy bid for photography equipment and the Martins want a rare stamp collection. S1, Ep11
North Carolina. The buyers are in North Carolina to bid on lost, damaged and misplaced freight. They all compete for a box of war antiques, plus they bid on a cage of unknown items. S1, Ep12
Bust A Move. The Kellys must find gold to pay off their debts. Shawn moves his camp in search of the motherlode, and Vernon's diver tries to mine without a light. S10, Ep25
Hustle And Overflow. Shawn is driven to desperate measures to solve his water overflow problems. Meanwhile, Vernon follows the gold trail despite dangerous ice conditions. S10, Ep26
The Heli Hunters go for a remote camping trip in the Murchison region of Western Australia. Near Gwalia, rookie team the Brumbies, can't seem to catch a break. S9, Ep6
Return Of The Outback Beast. Jeremy heads to Australia to investigate an underwater attack. Could it be the work of a giant fresh water predator that many believed to be extinct? S1, Ep7
Stay Focused Or Die. The typhoon has sunk one of the boats. But as the weather clears the fleet can't dwell on the tragedy and heads back out on the treacherous seas. S5, Ep3
Put Up or Shut Up. It's the 2008 King Crab season in Dutch Harbour, so get prepared for more high drama on the treacherous and deadly Bering Sea. S5, Ep4
Dragon's Teeth. Darrell focuses on a multi-million-dollar wreck tied to Sir Francis Drake. He and his team race to locate a treacherous area identified on the map as Dragon's Teeth. S2, Ep5
The Real Robin Hood. Josh Gates journeys across England to uncover the true story behind Robin Hood. He explores underground tunnels and finds what may be his final resting place. S2, Ep2
England's Vanished Crown Jewels. Josh is on a quest to find the legendary lost treasure of King John. He explores the marshlands of England to find the despised king's crown jewels. S3, Ep13
Nevada Thirst. The Kondors' homestead turns to dust and Marty gambles everything to save it. The Raney's discover infested trailers, searing heat and sand storms. S1, Ep5
Bearanoia. The Raney's are called to a failing Homestead in Colorado. Plus, Don makes a 40 mile commute each day leaving Lorinda alone and terrified of the bears and mountain lions. S1, Ep6
Aerial Opal Spotting. The mining season is almost over and Col's crew take one last gamble. The Cooke brothers strive to save their mega opal machine and disastrous season. S1, Ep8
Rookie Mistakes. With Dan stuck at home, Justin starts the new mining season alone. He is dealt a huge blow when their rich underground mine has been pegged by another miner. S2, Ep1
5-Year Storm Part 1. A menacing storm moves into the fleet, with a rogue wave ripping steel at the Cape Caution. Jake, a freshman skipper, struggles to battle through the winds. S11, Ep12
5-Year Storm Part 2. A 600-mile-wide arctic storm continues to ravage the fleet, and rookie skippers Jake Anderson and Josh Harris struggle just to keep their heads above water. S11, Ep13
A Tiger Ate My Face. Hashmot Ali had his face torn away by a tiger, and Yulianna Yussef is covered with hundreds of hairy birthmarks. Can doctors effectively treat them? S5, Ep1
Ants In My Head. An Indian girl suffers from an infestation of ants in her ear canal. And, a Brazilian woman's tiny facial birthmark has become a huge tumour despite 19 surgeries. S5, Ep2
A game changing piece of equipment leads the Ferals to their biggest nugget haul of the season. Plus, Shane and Russell battle unseasonal weather. S6, Ep11
